As well as being a solo artist, I am also co-founder of Independent UK Record Label Boltfish Recordings. My music often delves into the style of playful nursery rhyme tunes accompanied by stuttering beats and atmospheres or heartfelt cinematic compositions. 

Solo releases and compilation tracks have appeared on Boltfish Recordings and various labels including The Ministry of Sound, Duotone Records, LacedMilk, Kahvi, Raw42 Music, Yuki Yaki, October Man, ClickClickDrone, Aerotone, Rednetic, U-Cover and others.

I also write and record under my real name: Murray Fisher (Soundcloud link shown below) as well as collaborating with other artists.
I'm always happy to work on remixes, commissions or license my tracks for compilations, so message me if you have a project in mind.

La band, nata dalle costole di un'altro gruppo elettronico, i Killing M.A.T.E.R.I.A. , riprende le tematiche tanto care ad Autechre ed Aphex Twin mischiandole con le frequenze abrasive vicine a John Zorn, con il dubstep di Burial, Kode9, 2562, con la sperimentazione dei Box e con un certo tipo di drum 'n bass. Il tutto "condito" da passaggi al limite dell'industrial. A differenza dei gia citati KM, gli H3 No Dub : Experimental White Noise si addentrano su territori piu' ostici. Partendo da un certo tipo di "drone" ci si addentra fra synthz "disturbati" e continue alterazioni del suono. Come un richiamo dell'analogico e della vecchia puntina "crea-fruscio" del giradischi. The Dust Kills All Sound e' in pratica un doppio album (circa 80 minuti), che comprende diversi approcci sonori. Il disco alterna momenti tipicamente elettronici a sperimentazioni "alterate" con i moduli disturbanti della Bit Machine. Rumori, spazi vuoti, frequenze distorte sono volutamente create e ricercate (come dire, nessun "graffio" sul cd...) . Come se Aphex Twin flirtasse con il drone, come se Burial suonasse pezzi di un John Zorn in versione industrial.

Music Review - http://mureview.blogspot.com/
This blog is mainly going to be focused on electronic music reviews for net labels. There seems to be a serious lack of decent reviews for then, especially when compared with the amount of music being released by net labels every day. I often find the sheer amount of labels overwhelming and can't help but think that I'm missing out on lots of amazing music because i don't have enough time to listen to everything. The plan is to host as many reviews as are possible to get through.

If a label wants to submit music for a review get in touch via mureview@googlemail.com with a subject line of "Review" and a link to the tracks.

Likewise, if anyone would like to contribute reviews get in touch via mureview@googlemail.com with a subject line of "Writing"

Michal Poncar started his playing in 1993 under a name DJ Face. In that times it was just in small places near Prague. As an eager Radio 1 listener he met B√©la N√©meshegyi and very soon he started to write reviews for B√©la..s Pareniste server under a nickname Myclick. In 1999 he was also contributing with reviews of new records to Tripmag magazine thanks to Honza Babka who was editor in chief in that time. One year later, after his work for Trance.cz server, Mellow with Dan Kafka offered him a collaboration with Techno.cz. After reviews with unbelievable 13.000 types he is enjoying writting of voluminous reports from the events he took part in. He is preparing news from the world of dance music for this website and publishes DJ beginners..sets. Since 2004 you can hear him two times a week on Akropolis Internet Radio in programmes Techno.cz on Akropolis Radio and Techno.cz In Da Mix where he is interviewing DJs and mixing live sets right in studio. House in all its periods was his favourite. But there was basic change at the end of 2001 and the beginning of 2002. Then he was contacted by Lucas Ross the guitar player, Mataro purchased electronic percussion and Face 2 Face project had got its roughcast. Every performance took place with different guests and with different repertory. Five musician formation Face 2 Face with records and live instruments combination was performing beside small clubs also at Sazava Fest, Creamfields and several times in Roxy Club. DJ Face currently enjoys first of all nu disco, deep house, dubby house and minimal house and an ideal performance is to him a nights Unplugged @ House boat U Bukanyra and House 4 Adults @ 2. patro with DJ Cubik. At the beginning of 2010 the circle closes and his big dream comes true... Side by side with his friends who he called about his musical wishes to the Radio 1 in the mid of 90th, now he puts its own radio show Fluffy Clouds with legendary FlyBoyEda and soon with his longtime back 2 back partner in crime Diom every odd Sunday 15:00 - 18:00. Sydney-based, British born DJ, D-Funk has amassed a fair few achievements in his 25-years on the decks. Making his club debut at The Depot in Bristol in 1995, he‚Äôs gone on to DJ all over the world, playing notable sets at Space Ibiza and Ministry Of Sound and released on labels including Sunday Best and Bombstrikes. 

Getting his first set of decks at 14, Doug initially fell for the sounds of jungle and techno before a night dancing to house icon Tony De Vit in 1997 turned him towards the slinkier sounds of house music. 

His DJ career began to take off during his time at university in Wolverhampton where he started to pick up gigs at the Canal Club and Mezzanine, playing alongside DJs including Joey Negro, Mr Fingers, Scott Bond and Lisa Lashes, before a move to the South-Coast town of Bournemouth led him to eventually start his own night ‚ÄòBreak Da House‚Äô in 2004. 

The night took off, attracting big names including The Stanton Warriors and Plump DJs and eventually led to D-Funk‚Äôs first release, the ‚ÄòElectrotek‚Äô EP after Dub Pistols headlined one night and Barry Ashworth from the band decided to release Doug‚Äôs music on his Westway label. The track found its way onto a TV ad in Portugal, as well as becoming a mainstay on Kiss FM‚Äôs breakbeat chart and gave Doug the confidence to pursue a career as a producer as well as a DJ, eventually leading to releases on Adapted Records and Ghetto Funk among countless other labels over the next 15 years. 

Moving to Sydney Australia in 2009, Doug started his label Upstart Music, releasing his own productions alongside tracks from the likes of Crackerz & Jam, Niko & Lyall and Rogue Robot and later started the funk label Grits N Gravy alongside friend and funk producer Philly Blunt, with the label winning the ‚ÄòBest Label‚Äô award at Perth Dance Music Awards in 2010. 

Since living in Sydney, Doug has held down residencies at The World Bar and The Standard for the best part of a decade, as well as regular slots at Sash, Ivy and Hugos. But there was still demand for him back on the side of the world and he regularly returned to Europe to play at Space Ibiza (including a set at the penultimate night of Carl Cox‚Äôs Revolution party) as well as touring in the UK, Europe and Canada. 

Now 25 years into his career, Doug is about to mark the 10th anniversary of his label Grits ‚ÄòN‚Äô Gravy, with a compilation due this year mixed by himself and Philly Blunt, and has been busy producing house, hip hop and nu-disco with his current production partner Mr Doris.

dee3 (IRL: Don Voorhies) is ‚Äì in the lack of better terms ‚Äì a DK-based DJ.
An U.S. ex-pat, debuting behind the wheels of steel at the age of 14 during the tailgate of the disco-era in 1979, he continued on spinning on the mobile-scene and on-and-off in the club-scene in Jutland until 1986-87, when he started doing radio-work and spinning full-time as a club-DJ, until early 1991.

Later on, after gaining a Masters-degree in Information Science, he started in the early noughties working with and trying out a plethora of various computer-based DJ platforms that were then appearing on the market.

While trying out these various computer-based DJ platforms, he started compiling and mixing a mix-series called ‚ÄùCompiling a Network‚Äù and later on another mix-series called ‚Äùdee3 | datamixes‚Äù; these two - now merged - mix-series' 23 sets have now combined seen more than 2 million downloads from listeners spread out over more than 180 countries.

Furthermore, he has had mix sets that have been featured on several websites and blogs and/or aired as guest.sets on netradio-stations such as: The "No Watches, No Maps"-show (KSS Records netradio), Dimitri Pike's Teknology-show (livesets.com), flex.is ( Radio X, Reykjav√≠k - Iceland), The HumanJava website, the Thinner-label website, the dubtechnoblog.com website, the 6ONE6-label website, periskop.cc website, Suatec, technopodcast.com, The "Against Silence"-netradio, The "2B Continued"-netradio and Chunk-FM (fnoob techno radio) - just to name a few and more are definitely to come! Stay tuned...

Edu del Doce (as known as Hitch and one of the RAUM resident djs) is an artist that is clearly different and distinguished from the standard model of artists within today¬¥s nightlife panorama. The quality that stands out most in this highly experienced artist is his elegant and dynamic style which is easily recognizable in all of its facets. Another impressive quality that Deldoce possesses is his versatility and ability to resist getting caught up in any passing musical trend. All of his sets are fueled by a fresh, energetic and innovative vibe. These characteristics, among others, represent the true essence of this great professional. Deldoce¬¥s keen ability to adapt to any musical style or trend (deep house, minimal and tech house), together with his true connection with the demanding night crowd have contributed to shape his unique style, and have boosted him to an impressive position amongst the most recognizable and promising artists of today¬¥s musical panorama. 

With his expansive degree of experience, including performances throughout country of Spain and the rest of Europe (since 1997), this multifaceted artist is now seeking to adjust his professional path a bit, and has begun focusing clearly on the realm of musical production (working for some different labels such as DEEP CLASS, YOUNG ODDS, KHAZUMA, MATRA VIBES, NOVO MUSIC, BEDROOM MUZIK, 76 RECORDS, MUSIC TRAX REC, among others). Edu del Doce¬¥s performances and resident positions have been valued in the best clubs in Barcelona, Ibiza and other cities around Spain and Europe.

Also, Edu del Doce is one of the RAUM resident Djs.

Born in Minsk in 1984, Seahawk has had a strange affinity for music since he was a boy, and it got stronger and stronger as time passed. Influenced with great music of Robert Miles, Paul Van Dyk, Schiller, Angelo Badalamenti and others he started searching for his favourite styles in very different genres of electronica. 

In 2005, inspired by such DJ's as Shah and Pedro Del Mar, Markus Schulz, Andy Moor, producers from russian progressive scene and after clubbing for a while he decided to enter the magical world of mixing. In his sets he aspires to showcase different sound combinations, from breaks to deep, from progressive to trance which are the closest to his inner thoughts, providing an overwhelming voyage to discover new elegant and exquisite sonorities. 

Seahawk is a resident of DeepSounds radio where he hosts the ‚ÄúSilk Music‚Äù radioshow which is supported by the ‚ÄúSilk Digital Records‚Äù, Russia. Many talented dj‚Äôs and producers are expected to take part as guests here. The show is aired every 4th Saturday, 17:00 [GMT].

After their first label release on the infamous Moving Shadow Records in 2005, GEIN's signature style of heavy breaks has been a staple in the Drum & Bass scene worldwide. Defying standards and definition, their carefully crafted drums and relentless basslines have helped shape the darker side of DnB and gained a cult following. Now operating as an army of one, GEIN continues to break the mold with a his sonic arsenal of technical, nuanced and aggressive music.

In addition to Moving Shadow, he's released on other heavy hitting labels such as Tech Itch Recordings, Freak Recordings, Human Imprint, Evol Intent Records, PRSPCT, Algorythm Recordings and more. As well as collaborated with and remixed artists such as Technical Itch, Counterstrike, Audio, Sinister Souls, Cooh, DJ Hidden, Evol Intent to name a few.

GEIN is poised to come into 2018 swinging with original releases, collabs & international tours that you wont want to miss.

Spiriakos is a Czech techno matador based in Prague, whose name has been a matter of respect and admiration for clubbers and other artists for many years. Influenced by 90¬¥ Detroit techno and electro sound, Spiriakos installs a captivating atmosphere during his sets while using scratching and a wide range of effects.

History dates back to 2006 when he first touched the mix. One year later, Spiriakos started his career as a solo DJ, who gradually worked his way up from local events to the most significant Czech techno parties. Thanks to his diligence and originality, Spiriakos was soon considered one of the few designated as the representative of a new generation of techno DJs and producers and slowly gained respect among colleagues abroad, from whose he formerly drew his inspiration. Gigs in Slovenia, Poland, Italy, or Germany were not obliged to wait long. One of the biggest highlights has been a gig in legendary Berlin club Tresor.

His production sound is strongly influenced by The Advent and his musical vision. Niche signature tracks typical for their dense bassline and soft kick drum accompanied by a hypnotic synth sound has seen the support of names on the scene, such as The Advent, Tiga, Zombie Nation, Sasha Carassi, Filterheadz, A. Paul, Industrialyzer, Spiros Kaloumens, Dave Clarke, Virgil Enzinger, and many more. Over the years, Spiriakos has managed to release over 40 digital EPs and 7 vinyl records. However, always tries to improve his sound and make the best of himself with every upcoming EP.

After a short break, Spriakos immersed himself in the studio work, developing his production style and testing new hardware. In 2020 he returned with the house EP "Let's make love" on the Climax Digital Records label, showcasing his even broader musical focus. His solo project has, however, remained mainly focused on live performance and techno production. Moreover, Spiriakos became a part of the District 313 techno project, together with his long-term mate Makarov/Marvel 83. Their first Collapse EP on Phobiq was released in early 2022.

The idea behind the label is the ability to transmit futuristic frequencies with any available resources. By selecting and presenting audio material with the power to change, our endeavours are focused on overcoming the mediocre audio programming that is being fed to the planet, creating barriers within our minds and between civilizations. Using the science of creation to transcend percieved limitations. Connecting the advances in our culture and technology with the important lessons of visionaries that came before us.

The vinyl record is the symbol of DJ culture even in the time of digital mixing and auto-syncing. It represents more than just the physical form or the tangible aspect of DJ-ing. It is the medium whose cyclical movement best represents time itself. And in the end, all music is temporal art.

The art of the DJ mix is finding a space in time where the output becomes greater than just the sum of its parts. It could be an unexpected sensation, a great sequence of songs or that moment where two records fit together so seamlessly, so perfectly, they merge into a new entity.

We choose to enter the abyss of modern electronic output to share our vision of the future. A future that is not based on flavor-of-the-week hype but one that is built on the experience of a life-long journey.

This is our mission statement.

Over the past 15 years the internationally renowned Botchit and Scarper label has amassed an impressive roster of artists and an astounding back catalogue of releases that has ensured it has remained at the forefront of electronic music and continued to prosper through the unrelenting evolution of the music industry.

Established in 1995 by business partners Vini Medley and Martin Love, the founders of pioneering Jungle record label SOUR, Botchit has gone from strength to strength thanks to its forward thinking and progressive music policy and its unique emphasis on artist development and loyalty. 

Releasing over 70 singles and 30 LPs, Botchit has played a key role in helping to break acclaimed artists like Atomic Hooligan, Aquasky, FreQ Nasty and Deekline & Wizzard as well as continuing to support artists like T Power and B.L.I.M. (who had previously been housed on the SOUR and Emotif record labels) as they started to explore new territory. In more recent times, the label has been helping to push more new talent with releases from exciting prospects like Flore and Son Of Kick. 

Unwilling to be restricted by genre or scene and never afraid to step out of the box and challenge people, the label has had a number of ground-breaking releases ranging from FreQ Nasty‚Äôs ‚ÄòBoomin Back Atcha‚Äô featuring Pheobe One to Eddy Temple Morris‚Äô ‚ÄòDance Rocks‚Äô and Atomic Hooligan's ‚ÄòSex, Drugs and Blah Blah Blah‚Äô.
